Inspirations
------------

Successor stands on a lot of other people's ideas. The most direct
debts:

  Cheng Lou's Pretext  — the prepare-once / cache-by-target-size
                         pattern that powers BrailleArt.layout() and
                         PreparedText.lines() in the renderer.

  Hermes Agent + the   — the agent loop's continuation pattern
  open-source agent      (stream, detect tool call, execute, feed
  harness ecosystem      result back, repeat) and the convergence on
                         native chat-template tool calls.

  The open-source AI   — llama.cpp's OpenAI-compatible HTTP surface,
  community              the open-weight model families that make
                         local agentic chat useful, and the inference
                         tooling that turned this from a cloud-only
                         toy into something a single developer can
                         run on a laptop.

If your project deserves credit and is missing here, open an issue
on the repo. I would rather over-credit than under-credit.

If you build something cool with Successor, I would love to hear
about it.
